ial application. Please visit the Commercial Ramps page for these states and for a more robust commercial ramp system.\r\n\r\nIn residential use, modular wheelchair ramps do not require a building permit in most cases since they are not considered permanent structures and are not being used for public access. However, please check with your local building dept. for laws governing your location before purchasing the PVI modular wheelchair ramp system.\r\n\r\n<span style=\"color: #993300;\"><em>Handrails and adjustable legs are included.</em></span>\r\n\r\nWIDTH - 36\" standard - custom widths are available\r\nLENGTH - As Needed\r\nLOAD CAPACITY - Per code - 100 lbs. per square foot\r\nSLOPE - Adjustable - as required (1:12 recommended)\r\nFLOOR SURFACE - Slip Resistant grooved aluminum\r\nEDGE PROTECTION - 4\" Curb\r\nHANDRAILS - Double 1.5\" bar – standard height 36\" – 38\"\r\nMeets all code requirements for load specifications.\r\nRamps can be designed in an endless number of layout configurations.\r\nADA compliant at 1:12 slope, under 30\" in rise. Except in CA and MA.\r\n\r\n<span style=\"color: #993300;\"><strong>Shipping is included for the lower 48 States.</strong></span>\r\n\r\n<strong>PVI Modular XP Wheelchair Ramps</strong>\r\n<table>\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<th>Model</th>\r\n<th>DIMENSIONS</th>\r\n<th>PRICE</th>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>MXP2</td>\r\n<td>2\' x 36\"</td>\r\n<td>598.00</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>MXP3</td>\r\n<td>3\' x 36\"</td>\r\n<td>648.00</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>MXP4</td>\r\n<td>4\' x 36\"</td>\r\n<td>739.00</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>MXP5</td>\r\n<td>5\' x 36\"</td>\r\n<td>939.00</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>MXP6</td>\r\n<td>6\' x 36\"</td>\r\n<td>1074.00</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>MXP7</td>\r\n<td>7\' x 36\"</td>\r\n<td>1219.00</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>MXP8</td>\r\n<td>8\' x 36\"</td>\r\n<td>1369.00</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>MXP9</td>\r\n<td>9\' x 36\"</td>\r\n<td>1509.00</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>MXP10</td>\r\n<td>10\