'http://localhost:8888/disabilitysystems/?p=130',0,'revision','',0),(131,1,'2023-05-16 17:08:39','2023-05-16 17:08:39','','Sample Page','','inherit','closed','closed','','2-revision-v1','','','2023-05-16 17:08:39','2023-05-16 17:08:39','',2,'http://localhost:8888/disabilitysystems/?p=131',0,'revision','',0),(132,1,'2023-05-16 21:55:56','2023-05-16 21:55:56','<!-- wp:heading --><h2>Who we are</h2><!-- /wp:heading --><!-- wp:paragraph --><p><strong class=\"privacy-policy-tutorial\">Suggested text: </strong>Our website address is: http://localhost:8888/disabilitysystems.</p><!-- /wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:heading --><h2>Comments</h2><!-- /wp:heading --><!-- wp:paragraph --><p><strong class=\"privacy-policy-tutorial\">Suggested text: </strong>When visitors leave comments on the site we collect the data shown in the comments form, and also the visitor&#8217;s IP address and browser user agent string to help spam detection.</p><!-- /wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:paragraph --><p>An anonymized string created from your email address (also called a hash) may be provided to the Gravatar service to see if you are using it. The Gravatar service privacy policy is available here: https://automattic.com/privacy/. After approval of your comment, your profile picture is visible to the public in the context of your comment.</p><!-- /wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:heading --><h2>Media</h2><!-- /wp:heading --><!-- wp:paragraph --><p><strong class=\"privacy-policy-tutorial\">Suggested text: </strong>If you upload images to the website, you should avoid uploading images with embedded location data (EXIF GPS) included. Visitors to the website can download and extract any location data from images on the website.</p><!-- /wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:heading --><h2>Cookies</h2><!-- /wp:heading --><!-- wp:paragraph --><p><strong class=\"privacy-policy-tutorial\">Suggested text: </strong>If you leave a comment on our site you may opt-in to saving your name, email address and website in cookies. These are for your convenience so that you do not have to fill in your details again when you leave another comment. These cookies will last for one year.</p><!-- /wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:paragraph --><p>If you visit our login page, we will set a temporary cookie to determine if your browser accepts cookies. This cookie contains no personal data and is discarded when you close your browser.</p><!-- /wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:paragraph --><p>When you log in, we will also set up several cookies to save your login information and your screen display choices. Login cookies last for two days, and screen options cookies last for a year. If you select &quot;Remember Me&quot;, your login will persist for two weeks. If you log out of your account, the login cookies will be removed.</p><!-- /wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:paragraph --><p>If you edit or publish an article, an additional cookie will be saved in your browser. This cookie includes no personal data and simply indicates the post ID of the article you just edited. It expires after 1 day.</p><!-- /wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:heading --><h2>Embedded content from other websites</h2><!-- /wp:heading --><!-- wp:paragraph --><p><strong class=\"privacy-policy-tutorial\">Suggested text: </strong>Articles on this site may include embedded content (e.g. videos, images, articles, etc.). Embedded content from other websites behaves in the exact same way as if the visitor has visited the other website.</p><!-- /wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:paragraph --><p>These websites may collect data about you, use cookies, embed additional third-party tracking, and monitor your interaction with that embedded content, including tracking your interaction with the embedded content if you have an account and are logged in to that website.</p><!-- /wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:heading --><h2>Who we share your data with</h2><!-- /wp:heading --><!-- wp:paragraph --><p><strong class=\"privacy-policy-tutorial\">Suggested text: </strong>If you request a password reset, your IP address will be included in the reset email.</p><!-- /wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:heading --><h2>How long we retain your data</h2><!-- /wp:heading --><!-- wp:paragraph --><p><strong class=\"privacy-policy-tutorial\">Suggested text: </strong>If you leave a comment, the comment and its metadata are retained indefinitely. This is so we can recognize and approve any follow-up comments automatically instead of holding them in a moderation queue.</p><!-- /wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:paragraph --><p>For users that register on our website (if any), we also store the personal information they provide in their user profile. All users can see, edit, or delete their personal information at any time (except they cannot change their username). Website administrators can also see and edit that information.</p><!-- /wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:heading --><h2>What rights you have over your data</h2><!-- /wp:heading --><!-- wp:paragraph --><p><strong class=\"privacy-policy-tutorial\">Suggested text: </strong>If you have an account on this site, or have left comments, you can request to receive an exported file of the personal data we hold about you, including any data you have provided to us. You can also request that we erase any personal data we hold about you. This does not include any data we are obliged to keep for administrative, legal, or security purposes.</p><!-- /wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:heading --><h2>Where your data is sent</h2><!-- /wp:heading --><!-- wp:paragraph --><p><strong class=\"privacy-policy-tutorial\">Suggested text: </strong>Visitor comments may be checked through an automated spam detection service.</p><!-- /wp:paragraph -->','Privacy Policy','','inherit','closed','closed','','3-revision-v1','','','2023-05-16 21:55:56','2023-05-16 21:55:56','',3,'http://localhost:8888/disabilitysystems/?p=132',0,'revision','',0),(134,1,'2023-05-16 21:58:10','2023-05-16 21:58:10','<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Disability Systems, Inc. Privacy Statement, Terms, Return Policy</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>This privacy statement discloses the privacy practices for Disability Systems, Inc. and terms of service which includes return policy and shipping statement. If you feel that this company is not abiding by its posted privacy policy, you should contact Disability Systems, Inc. by phone at 1-877-258-7423 or email at&nbsp;<a href=\"mailto:privacy@disabilitysystems.com\">info@disabilitysystems.com</a>.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Information Collection and Use</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Disability Systems, Inc. is the sole owner of the information collected on this site. We will not sell, share, or rent this information to others.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Secure Shopping Cart Order Form</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>We request information from the user on our order form. Here a user must provide contact information (like name and shipping address) and financial information (like credit card number, expiration date). This information is used for billing purposes and to fill customer’s orders. If we have trouble processing an order, this contact information is used to get in touch with the user.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Credit Card and Shipping Companies</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>We use an outside shipping company to ship orders, and a secure credit card processing company to bill users for goods and services. These companies do not retain, share, store or use personally identifiable information for any secondary purposes. These parties are not allowed to use personally identifiable information except for the purpose of providing these services.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Charging Your Credit Card</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Credit cards will be charged the day your order is placed.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Purchase Orders</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>We will accept PO#\'s from established companies only. Please email your PO to&nbsp;<a href=\"mailto:info@disabilitysystems.com\">info@disabilitysystems.com</a>&nbsp;Please call us at 1-877-258-7423 to confirm we have received the order.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Service Area</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>North America, USA, Canada, AL, AK, AZ, AR, CA, CO, CT, DE, FL, GA, HI, ID, IL, IN, IA,KS, KY, LA, ME, MD, MA, MI, MN, MS, MO, MT, NE, NV, NH, NJ, NM, NY, NC, ND, OH, OK, OR, PA, PR, RI, SC, SD, TN, TX, UT, VT, VI, VA, WA, WV, WI, WY</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Links</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>This website contains links to other sites. Please be aware that Disability Systems, Inc. is not responsible for the privacy practices of other sites. We encourage our users to be aware when they leave our site and to read the privacy statements of each and every website that collects personally identifiable information. This privacy statement applies solely to information collected by this Web site.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Security</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>This site has a secure shopping cart. We take every precaution to protect our users’ information. When users submit sensitive information via the website, your information is protected both online and off-line. When our order form asks users to enter sensitive information (such as credit card number, that information is encrypted and is protected with the best encryption software in the industry - SSL. While on a secure page, such as our shopping cart, the address bar of your browser will display the web page address beginning with the https indicating a secure connection.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>While our credit card processing company uses SSL encryption to protect sensitive information online, we also do everything in our power to protect user-information off-line. We actually never see your complete credit card number when you order over the Internet. We see only the last four digits. If you prefer to call your order in please dial 1-877-258-7423 and we\'ll be happy to get your information over the phone.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Return Policy</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>We will make every effort to replace a defective product that you have purchased from our website as soon as possible. Before you return any item to either us or the manufacturer you must call us between the hours of 9am-5pm, Mountain Time, Monday through Friday at 1-877-258-7423 so that we can work with you in replacing or returning an item.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Products which have been installed or used and are not in a \"like new\" condition can not be returned for credit. Only defective products can be returned for replacement. In the case of door openers, we can not accept returns for units that are functioning properly but only need field adjustments. It is your responsibility to read and understand the instructions and adjustment options available for your door opener. We can not accept returns on items that only require adjustments to operate properly.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Returned items must be returned within 30 days of purchase and in their original boxes in like new condition and properly packaged so as not to damage the product in shipping. Again, please call us at 1-877-258-7423 to obtain a proper shipping address for the product you are returning. Returns will not be accepted after 30 days from the date of purchase. Returned items are subject to a 20% restocking and handling fee charge plus freight both ways. Items returned in a damaged or used condition will have a 30% restock fee.&nbsp; There may be additional charges if the product is returned in damaged condition.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>We cannot accept returns on installed (used) door openers, activation switches, sensors, timers, custom ramps, folding ramps, portable ramps or modular wheelchair ramp systems. We will help our customers with any manufacturer warranty claims for our products.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Shipping</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Free Shipping applies to the contiguous United States and only on products identified as including free shipping on the Website.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Most orders placed before 12:00 PM mountain time are shipped the same day. Orders placed after 12:00 PM are shipped the following day with the exception of orders placed on Fridays after 12:00 PM. Those orders will ship on the following Monday. Custom orders can take up to three weeks to complete depending on the complexity of the order. We will notify you by phone or email if your order is out of stock with an estimated delivery time. Products that include free shipping as part of their price can take up to two weeks to arrive at your door (in the contiguous US only.) You always have the option to call us immediately after placing your order at 1-877-258-7423 to request optional shipping methods. The cost for alternative shipping will vary depending on your needs. We assume no responsibility for missed delivery dates due to circumstances beyond our control such as postal, UPS or freight company errors or an incorrect postal address given while placing your order.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Disability Systems, Inc.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>6834 S. University Blvd. Box 222</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Centennial, CO 80122-1515</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>1-877-258-7423<a href=\"mailto:info@disabilitysystems.com\">info@disabilitysystems.com</a></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','Privacy Policy','','inherit','closed','closed','','3-revision-v1','','','2023-05-16 21:58:10','2023-05-16 21:58:10','',3,'http://localhost:8888/disabilitysystems/?p=134',0,'revision','',0),(135,1,'2023-05-16 22:02:33','2023-05-16 22:02:33','','Sample Page','','inherit','closed','closed','','2-revision-v1','','','2023-05-16 22:02:33','2023-05-16 22:02:33','',2,'http://localhost:8888/disabilitysystems/?p=135',0,'revision','',0),(136,1,'2023-05-17 12:49:19','2023-05-17 12:49:19','','Sample Page','','inherit','closed','closed','','2-revision-v1','','','2023-05-17 12:49:19','2023-05-17 12:49:19','',2,'http://localhost:8888/disabilitysystems/?p=136',0,'revision','',0),(137,1,'2023-05-17 12:49:49','2023-05-17 12:49:49','','Sample Page','','inherit','closed','closed','','2-revision-v1','','','2023-05-17 12:49:49','2023-05-17 12:49:49','',2,'http://localhost:8888/disabilitysystems/?p=137',0,'revision','',0),(138,1,'2023-05-17 14:40:57','2023-05-17 14:40:57','','Door-Controls-Working-with-Disability-Systems','','inherit','open','closed','','door-controls-working-with-disability-systems','','','2023-05-17 14:41:03','2023-05-17 14:41:03','',90,'http://localhost:8888/disabilitysystems/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Door-Controls-Working-with-Disability-Systems.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(139,1,'2023-05-17 14:41:52','2023-05-17 14:41:52','','Door Controls','','inherit','closed','closed','','90-revision-v1','','','2023-05-17 14:41:52','2023-05-17 14:41:52','',90,'http://localhost:8888/disabilitysystems/?p=139',0,'revision','',0),(140,1,'2023-05-17 14:46:11',